cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.AR 

This paper discusses the principles and system performance of wireless device-to-device (D2D) caching networks, which are related to topics in networking (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), millimeter-wave communication (cs.MM), system engineering (cs.SY), and architecture (cs.AR). The paper specifically focuses on the throughput scaling laws of these networks, which are fundamental to information theory and networking.
